description._content: View of crowds at Mt. Victoria in 1913, celebrating centenary of first European crossing of the Blue Mountains, with dignitaries, tents and banners and unidentified photographer in background. This image is part of a collection entitled ‘Blue Mountains - Monuments and Celebrations', which is available to view on the Royal Australian Historical Society's Historypin Channel. Access the collection at the following link: www.historypin.com/channels/view/id/48441/#|collections/v... Please feel free to comment on this or any of the other images in the collection. If you have more accurate information regarding the location and/or date of the image, we would love to hear from you!
